Faced with this question, McCarthy paused briefly and looked down at the ground, clearly caught off guard.
He then began his desperate answer with a pseudo-profound truism: “Well, times change as it moves forward,” he said.
He continued: “When you get the more report of the drugs coming across, you get the more reports of human trafficking and others.
And while unauthorized border crossings were up somewhat after 2017, they are still well below recent peaks — and this explanation still doesn’t show why the GOP didn’t declare a national emergency last year.
“Translation: We’re spineless cowards marching to the orders of Dear Leader, what do you want?” said national security lawyer Bradley Moss of McCarthy’s comments.